-- Kyowa Hakko Kirin Falls Most in 2 Months After Credit Suisse Cuts Rating
-- B y   G e a r o i d   R e i d y
-- 2011-02-10T00:14:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-10/kyowa-hakko-kirin-falls-most-in-2-months-after-credit-suisse-cuts-rating.html
Kyowa Hakko Kirin Co. fell the most
in two months in Tokyo trading after Credit Suisse Group AG cut
its rating for the Japanese drugmaker to “neutral”.   Kyowa Kirin lost 3.1 percent to 848 yen as of 9:13 a.m. on
the Tokyo Stock Exchange, headed for the biggest decline since
Dec. 7. The benchmark Nikkei 225 Stock Average fell 0.4 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gearoid Reidy at 
 greidy1@bloomberg.net  